        "text": "*[Bug 18913] Providing an accessor 'quiet()' to query the R_Quiet state from R*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18913>\n\n--- Comment #4 from Sebastian Meyer (<mailto:seb.meyer@fau.de|seb.meyer@fau.de>) ---\nCurrently\n\n    -q, --quiet           Don't print startup message\n    --verbose             Print more information about progress\n\nso `R_Quiet` has a very limited scope whereas `R_Verbose` is more generic and\nis indeed extensively used in base functions via `verbose =\ngetOption(\"verbose\")`.\n\nIf R provided access to R_Quiet, it would effectively extend its scope to a\n\"quiet mode\".\n\nWould it makes sense for some base functions to honour R_Quiet in their default\nbehaviour?\nThese have a `quiet` argument that defaults to FALSE:\n\n```\nR&gt; sapply(tools::standard_package_names()$base, function (pkg) { \n    m &lt;- eapply(getNamespace(pkg), \n                function(x) is.function(x) &amp;&amp; isFALSE(formals(x)[[\"quiet\"]]))\n    names(m)[unlist(m)]\n}) |&gt; Filter(f = length) |&gt; str(vec.len = Inf)\nList of 3\n $ base : chr [1:3] \"find.package\" \"scan\" \"path.package\"\n $ utils: chr [1:5] \"RtangleSetup\" \"RweaveLatexSetup\" \"timestamp\"\n\"download.file\" \"install.packages\"\n $ stats: chr [1:2] \"midcache.dendrogram\" \"addmargins\"\n```\n\nPersonally I use --quiet only indirectly via -s (--no-echo) in non-interactive\nruns, including from `Rscript`, `R CMD Sweave` or `R -s -e\n'&lt;anotherVignetteBuilder&gt;::&lt;anotherWeave&gt;()'`, and I think I would *not* want\ndownload.file() or any other function to then automatically switch to quiet\nmode.",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1751381738.346789",
        "bot_id": "B06769YJX9Q",
