                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " is more generic and\nis indeed extensively used in base functions via `verbose =\ngetOption(\"verbose\")`.\n\nIf R provided access to R_Quiet, it would effectively extend its scope to a\n\"quiet mode\".\n\nWould it makes sense for some base functions to honour R_Quiet in their default\nbehaviour?\nThese have a "
